        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 8:05PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 805 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Naola, or 7 miles east of Big Island, moving
southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail and wind gusts up to 30 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...

Locations impacted include...
Lynchburg...
Forest...
Coleman Falls...
Madison Heights...
Boonsboro...
Falconerville...
and Timberlake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
